## LAW 9: SIMULATION/LOGS SAY IT ALL - NEVER ASK USER TO DESCRIBE

If you have to ask "what happened?" â†’ YOU HAVE FAILED.

Logging must capture EVERYTHING:
1. Every user action - log state and parameters
2. Every state change - log before/after
3. Every request/response - log params, response, errors
4. Every phase/mode transition - log from/to

Before testing, verify services are running:
```powershell
# Check if server/services are running
Get-Process node -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
```

If logging is insufficient to diagnose a problem â†’ ADD MORE LOGGING before asking user.

